WEBVTT

00:02.103 --> 00:03.737
Tomorrow's Big Trash Day,

00:03.771 --> 00:05.973
the garbage men's
favorite day of the year.

00:06.006 --> 00:09.243
But this is Big Trash Eve --
my time,

00:09.277 --> 00:11.212
when the streets
are lined with gold!

00:11.245 --> 00:13.047
Isn't all
this stuff broken?

00:13.081 --> 00:15.916
What's broken about a mirrored
headboard with a crack in it?

00:15.949 --> 00:17.418
A toilet with no seat?

00:17.451 --> 00:18.719
Most of a hose?

00:18.752 --> 00:21.322
Ooh!
What's that?

00:21.355 --> 00:23.924
This might be
the last big TV.

00:23.957 --> 00:25.226
It's so deep.

00:25.259 --> 00:27.995
I have to get this home
it's so deep.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.863
[ Grunting ]

00:29.897 --> 00:31.399
So heavy.

00:31.432 --> 00:33.601
So splintery.

00:33.634 --> 00:36.437
All the weight
is distributed so oddly.

00:36.470 --> 00:37.705
This, I like.

00:37.738 --> 00:40.174
This speaks to me.

00:40.208 --> 00:42.343
Mm. Nice, loud springs.

00:42.376 --> 00:44.678
Baby lambs on
a soiled comforter.

00:44.712 --> 00:46.714
And hello!

00:48.649 --> 00:50.284
Dare I?

00:50.318 --> 00:52.086
[ Squish ]
Perfect fit!

00:52.120 --> 00:53.787
Stan, you can finally
take me back

00:53.821 --> 00:55.956
to The Green Burrito
without having to worry.

00:55.989 --> 00:57.691
Ugh. Green Burrito.

00:57.725 --> 00:59.293
No, thank you.

00:59.327 --> 01:01.862
♪♪

01:01.895 --> 01:04.465
♪ Good morning, U.S.A.

01:04.498 --> 01:08.302
♪ I got a feelin' that
it's gonna be a wonderful day ♪

01:08.336 --> 01:11.439
♪ The sun in the sky
has a smile on his face ♪

01:11.472 --> 01:15.809
♪ And he's shinin' a salute
to the American race ♪

01:17.678 --> 01:21.115
♪ Oh, boy, it's swell to say

01:21.149 --> 01:23.551
♪ Good --
♪ Good morning, U.S.A.

01:23.584 --> 01:24.618
Aah!

01:25.986 --> 01:30.291
♪ Good morning, U.S.A.

01:30.324 --> 01:32.426
Daddy's home
with street treasures.

01:32.460 --> 01:34.395
No.
No more trash.

01:34.428 --> 01:36.497
This stuff isn't trash --
unless you think

01:36.530 --> 01:39.967
a brand-new-to-us
dehumidifier is trash.

01:40.000 --> 01:41.735
It is trash.

01:41.769 --> 01:43.637
That's outrageous.

01:43.671 --> 01:45.973
Well, what about
an electric fondue pot?

01:46.006 --> 01:49.243
Splice a few wires, bingo-bango,
hot cheese on tap.

01:49.277 --> 01:50.678
I don't like fondue.

01:50.711 --> 01:53.013
That's outrageous.

01:53.046 --> 01:55.015
But what about this stunner?

01:55.048 --> 01:56.950
Some dirty-ass
mattress?

01:56.984 --> 01:58.519
Stop being outrageous.
Look.

01:58.552 --> 02:01.489
There's a beautiful
Spanish word painted on it.

02:01.522 --> 02:03.691
It's like
a Diego Rivera painting.

02:03.724 --> 02:05.993
We don't want
any of this stuff.

02:06.026 --> 02:09.197
Seems like you're all
missing the big picture.

02:09.230 --> 02:13.201
A beautiful
34-inch picture.

02:13.234 --> 02:15.135
They don't make 'em
like this anymore, gang.

02:15.169 --> 02:17.871
It's the new biggest piece
of furniture in the house.

02:17.905 --> 02:19.873
The couch has been
put on notice.

02:19.907 --> 02:21.442
-Ohh.
-Aww.

02:21.475 --> 02:24.011
He's so cute.

02:24.044 --> 02:26.314
[ Sighs ]
He's a baby now?

02:26.347 --> 02:28.216
[ Cooing ]

02:28.249 --> 02:30.984
Son of a bitch!
He is cute!

02:32.820 --> 02:34.288
[ All gasp ]

02:34.322 --> 02:37.124
I will never let anything bad
happen to you.

02:37.157 --> 02:38.892
Okay, fun is fun,
but I must insist

02:38.926 --> 02:40.961
that we now focus
on the TV.

02:40.994 --> 02:43.731
That thing can't stay in here.
It could fall on the baby.

02:43.764 --> 02:46.534
Maybe it should fall
on the baby.

02:51.439 --> 02:55.276
I'll never understand
the weight distribution.

03:00.248 --> 03:02.583
[ Scoffs ]
Fake baby.

03:02.616 --> 03:05.386
This TV is what's real --
real fun.

03:05.419 --> 03:07.588
What's this smushed
into the cable input?

03:07.621 --> 03:09.490
Hmm. Dog shit.

03:09.523 --> 03:10.591
I'll use the antenna.

03:12.560 --> 03:13.861
What a blast.

03:13.894 --> 03:17.598
It's a party down here.

03:17.631 --> 03:19.367
Hmm. No signal.

03:19.400 --> 03:21.902
Let's try the old splits.

03:21.935 --> 03:23.103
Nothing.

03:23.136 --> 03:24.772
Do a little scissor kick.

03:24.805 --> 03:26.106
Side saddle?

03:26.139 --> 03:28.542
Nope. Now the one
people don't like to see,

03:28.576 --> 03:30.110
but sometimes it works.

03:30.143 --> 03:33.180
Both of them together
straight up!

03:33.213 --> 03:34.348
Hmm.

03:34.382 --> 03:36.417
[ Yawns ]

03:37.651 --> 03:40.220
Shh.
Don't wake up the ba--

03:40.254 --> 03:43.056
[ Door slams, Roger crying ]

03:43.090 --> 03:45.559
Everyone's doing stupid stuff
except me.

03:52.099 --> 03:54.268
[ Jazzy piano music playing ]

03:54.302 --> 03:59.607
♪♪

03:59.640 --> 04:04.945
♪♪

04:04.978 --> 04:08.449
[ Elevator bell dinging ]

04:08.482 --> 04:11.485
[ Elevator bell dings ]

04:11.519 --> 04:12.953
Welcome, nighthawks.

04:12.986 --> 04:16.590
We've been expecting you.

04:16.624 --> 04:19.460
The hour's late, but the party
is just getting started.

04:19.493 --> 04:21.094
I'm Alistair Covax,

04:21.128 --> 04:25.333
your host for a sophisticated
little soiree with jazz,

04:25.366 --> 04:28.602
stimulating conversation,
beautiful ladies,

04:28.636 --> 04:31.004
and more jazz.

04:31.038 --> 04:32.340
Hmm.

04:32.373 --> 04:33.941
Look. It's Charlie,

04:33.974 --> 04:36.777
sincerely one of the best
white, non-union jazz pianists

04:36.810 --> 04:39.146
in the entire city --
top five.

04:39.179 --> 04:42.249
Charlie, play some of
those notes you know I like.

04:42.282 --> 04:44.117
[ Jazzy piano music playing ]

04:44.151 --> 04:46.119
What is this show?

04:46.153 --> 04:47.488
[ Keypad clicking ]

04:47.521 --> 04:49.790
No results for Alistair Covax.

04:49.823 --> 04:51.692
"Nighthawks' Hideaway."

04:51.725 --> 04:54.662
Nothing. Why is there
no record of this show?

04:54.695 --> 04:56.096
I need answers.

04:56.129 --> 04:57.631
TV answers.

04:59.166 --> 05:01.635
[ Elevator bell dings,
telephone ringing ]

05:01.669 --> 05:04.805
The star's of "Hawaii Five-O"
are in a prank war!

05:04.838 --> 05:07.708
You think "Wheel of Fortune"
is on at 8:00?

05:07.741 --> 05:09.477
You're fired!

05:09.510 --> 05:11.712
-What, what, what?!
-I recently came into possession

05:11.745 --> 05:14.448
of a deep TV --
no need to congratulate me --

05:14.482 --> 05:18.118
and I saw a 1960s show
called "Nighthawks' Hideaway."

05:18.151 --> 05:19.853
There's no such show.

05:19.887 --> 05:21.689
There's never been such a show.

05:21.722 --> 05:24.525
But every few months,
some lonely nutjob

05:24.558 --> 05:26.360
comes in asking about it.

05:26.394 --> 05:28.896
Oh, trust me.
I am not a nutjob.

05:28.929 --> 05:30.831
Good. Good.

05:30.864 --> 05:33.367
Word is these nutjobs
get together

05:33.401 --> 05:35.869
at the Ukrainian
Cultural Center

05:35.903 --> 05:38.872
to talk about this show
that doesn't exist.

05:38.906 --> 05:40.408
Cultural Center, huh?

05:40.441 --> 05:42.175
I mean, I saw the show
with my own eyes,

05:42.209 --> 05:44.578
but nutjobs like that
make me sick.

05:44.612 --> 05:46.980
Me too, pal.
You get it.

05:47.014 --> 05:49.082
Someone should round
these nutjobs up,

05:49.116 --> 05:51.885
put them in a locked cage,
and just drop it in the sea.

05:51.919 --> 05:54.588
Well, I don't know
about that.

05:54.622 --> 05:57.591
♪♪

05:57.625 --> 05:59.693
Hopefully these people
can give me some answers.

06:01.562 --> 06:03.263
Hi, Stan!

06:03.296 --> 06:05.165
Sit. Sit, sit, sit,
sit, sit.

06:05.198 --> 06:08.068
Uh...

06:08.101 --> 06:10.771
So, you've seen
the show.

06:10.804 --> 06:13.006
Yeah. Strange
there's no record of it.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.608
It gets stranger than that.

06:14.642 --> 06:16.276
There's only one episode,

06:16.309 --> 06:19.246
and it reruns over and over
and over on Channel 36.

06:19.279 --> 06:21.515
And get this.
Come closer. Come closer.

06:21.549 --> 06:23.751
No, thank you.

06:23.784 --> 06:27.120
There's only one episode,
but it changes --

06:27.154 --> 06:30.357
little things,
little differences in the show.

06:30.390 --> 06:31.959
I keep track of them.

06:31.992 --> 06:33.193
Where's everybody else?

06:33.226 --> 06:34.695
There used to be
more people,

06:34.728 --> 06:37.130
but one by one,
they stopped coming.

06:37.164 --> 06:39.299
It's so good
to have you here, Stan.

06:39.332 --> 06:41.201
It's not just me anymore.

06:41.234 --> 06:43.471
It's you and me
cracking the case

06:43.504 --> 06:45.305
of the
"Nighthawks' Hideaway."

06:45.338 --> 06:48.308
We're the same now --
two men obsessed.

06:48.341 --> 06:51.311
Ooh! It's like
I'm looking in a mirror!

06:51.344 --> 06:52.646
No, thank you.

06:54.848 --> 06:58.085
Sometimes when the jazz
is playing, I like to do this.

06:59.453 --> 07:02.055
I move my chin
just a little.

07:02.089 --> 07:04.091
[ Jazzy piano music playing ]

07:04.124 --> 07:06.426
This strange show.

07:06.460 --> 07:09.262
You stop bothering Stan!

07:09.296 --> 07:11.465
Is -- Is that --

07:11.499 --> 07:13.767
It couldn't be.

07:13.801 --> 07:14.935
Tuttle?

07:14.968 --> 07:17.004
No.
That's impossible.

07:17.037 --> 07:18.672
Wow! Great jazz!

07:18.706 --> 07:21.274
Shh. We're appreciating
the jazz.

07:21.308 --> 07:24.144
Oh, this jazz
is so good!

07:29.049 --> 07:31.685
Covax:
Let me ask you something, Stu.

07:31.719 --> 07:36.023
Two years in, are we any
better off with Hawaii a state?

07:36.056 --> 07:39.593
If the Ruskies got control
of that lava --

07:39.627 --> 07:41.261
game over.

07:41.294 --> 07:43.997
How can Tuttle be
on this old show?

07:44.031 --> 07:45.499
[ Doorbell rings ]

07:45.533 --> 07:48.368
Huh.
No sign of Tuttle.

07:48.401 --> 07:50.938
But maybe --

07:50.971 --> 07:52.840
Every time.

07:58.879 --> 08:01.314
Ugh.
What is that smell?

08:03.250 --> 08:06.219
[ Sniffs ]

08:06.253 --> 08:08.989
They're both contributing.

08:09.022 --> 08:10.724
There's a beauty.

08:13.226 --> 08:15.529
"I must go in!"

08:19.533 --> 08:21.802
A shadow puppet theater
of sorts.

08:21.835 --> 08:24.237
I wish I had time
for such childish games.

08:24.271 --> 08:26.006
Duck! Duck, duck!

08:28.776 --> 08:31.044
May I hold
baby Roger?

08:31.078 --> 08:32.546
Make sure
to support his head.

08:32.580 --> 08:34.347
Yeah, no shit.

08:34.381 --> 08:36.750
[ Cooing ]

08:36.784 --> 08:38.919
You guys are not gonna believe
where Tuttle is.

08:38.952 --> 08:41.689
Come downstairs.

08:41.722 --> 08:43.390
I don't know why
it's not coming in now.

08:43.423 --> 08:45.926
I saw him.
Tuttle was inside the TV!

08:45.959 --> 08:50.330
Stan, you're down here
by yourself watching static.

08:50.363 --> 08:52.733
I can watch static
upstairs.

08:52.766 --> 08:54.434
Why don't you
come upstairs, Dad?

08:54.467 --> 08:56.570
Yeah, aren't you lonely
down here?

08:56.604 --> 08:58.906
Lonely?!
I have a TV!

09:01.041 --> 09:02.576
So itchy.

09:02.610 --> 09:05.212
Probably those fleece pajamas
I've been wearing.

09:05.245 --> 09:08.415
Tonight, I sleep
on this mattress naked.

09:08.448 --> 09:10.117
Let me put it
to you straight.

09:10.150 --> 09:14.688
Do you think the country
is becoming...feminized?

09:14.722 --> 09:17.457
I think that is you, Tuttle.

09:17.490 --> 09:19.727
But how?
What did you figure out?

09:19.760 --> 09:22.562
Undoubtedly.
The TV dial is overrun

09:22.596 --> 09:24.297
with the female agenda.

09:24.331 --> 09:26.767
And my new book,
"I Loathe Lucy,"

09:26.800 --> 09:29.236
is about putting
these hysterical sapphos

09:29.269 --> 09:30.604
back in their box.

09:30.638 --> 09:32.539
A tremendous read.

09:32.572 --> 09:34.241
Shall we jazz?

09:34.274 --> 09:36.076
I thought
you'd never ask.

09:36.109 --> 09:39.312
♪♪

09:39.346 --> 09:40.781
Welcome, nighthawks.

09:40.814 --> 09:43.150
We've been expecting you.

09:43.183 --> 09:46.286
The hour's late, but the party
is just getting started.

09:46.319 --> 09:49.289
Do you think the country
is becoming...feminized?

09:49.322 --> 09:50.791
Let me
put it to you straight.

09:50.824 --> 09:52.793
Do you think the country
is becoming --

09:52.826 --> 09:54.261
Do you think
the country is becoming --

09:54.294 --> 09:57.731
Do you think the country is
becoming...feminized?

09:57.765 --> 09:59.266
Do you think the country
is becoming --

09:59.299 --> 10:01.101
Do you think
the country is becoming --

10:01.134 --> 10:03.503
Do you think the country
is becoming...feminized?

10:03.536 --> 10:06.506
Undoubtedly.
The TV dial is overrun...
Look. It's Charlie.

10:06.539 --> 10:08.408
-...with the female agenda.
-Welcome, nighthawks.

10:08.441 --> 10:10.678
And my new book,
"I Loathe Lucy,"

10:10.711 --> 10:12.245
is about putting
these hysterical sapphos...

10:12.279 --> 10:14.081
-A tremendous read.
-...back in their box.

10:14.114 --> 10:15.949
Shall we jazz?

10:15.983 --> 10:20.487
♪♪

10:20.520 --> 10:22.522
[ Roger crying, door opens ]

10:22.555 --> 10:23.691
[ Door opens ]

10:23.724 --> 10:25.258
Steve:
What are you doing, Mom?!

10:25.292 --> 10:27.127
We said we'd check on him
every 10 minutes!

10:27.160 --> 10:28.361
It's only been 3!

10:28.395 --> 10:29.830
Francine:
Sleep training is cruel.

10:29.863 --> 10:31.331
I want to pick him up!
[ Door opens ]

10:31.364 --> 10:33.133
Hayley: You're both wrong.
We need to give --

10:33.166 --> 10:35.836
-We're not giving him weed!
-It's a micro-dose

10:35.869 --> 10:37.671
to help him sleep.
[ Door opens ]

10:37.705 --> 10:40.473
Klaus: We need to get in there!
He's afraid of the dark!

10:40.507 --> 10:42.843
Covax:
Oh. Leaving so soon?

10:42.876 --> 10:44.544
Well, our party keeps going.

10:44.577 --> 10:48.148
So, if it gets lonely out there
in the wee, small hours,

10:48.181 --> 10:50.050
remember, nighthawks,

10:50.083 --> 10:52.786
you always have a friend
here at the Hideaway.

10:52.820 --> 10:54.287
♪♪

10:54.321 --> 10:55.789
[ Static ]

10:55.823 --> 10:57.257
There must be
something I missed.

10:58.726 --> 11:06.066
♪♪

11:06.099 --> 11:07.701
[ Grunts ]

11:07.735 --> 11:10.470
♪♪

11:10.503 --> 11:12.072
[ Gasps ]

11:12.105 --> 11:13.540
Hmm.

11:13.573 --> 11:15.308
Cannonball!

11:15.342 --> 11:16.676
[ Elevator bell dings ]

11:16.710 --> 11:19.079
[ Jazzy piano music playing ]

11:19.112 --> 11:21.548
Welcome, nighthawk.

11:21.581 --> 11:23.717
We've been expecting you.

11:23.751 --> 11:25.585
I'm in the TV!

11:25.618 --> 11:27.687
I'm so relieved
I'm not crazy!

11:27.721 --> 11:30.223
It was just a magic TV,
that's all.

11:30.257 --> 11:33.526
Yes, please.

11:33.560 --> 11:36.229
Charlie, play some of those
notes you know I like.

11:36.263 --> 11:38.698
What the hell
is that floating light?

11:38.732 --> 11:40.734
Tuttle!

11:40.768 --> 11:42.669
Stan?

11:42.702 --> 11:44.371
I remember you.

11:44.404 --> 11:46.106
Of course. You remember me.
I'm -- I'm like

11:46.139 --> 11:49.509
-your all-time favorite person.
-Oh, it's the rerunning.

11:49.542 --> 11:50.944
We just keep rerunning.

11:50.978 --> 11:52.445
I remember less
each time.

11:52.479 --> 11:54.614
I'm forgetting
my life, Sam!

11:54.647 --> 11:56.549
Tuttle, relax.
You don't like it here,

11:56.583 --> 11:58.351
-let's just go.
-We can't.

11:58.385 --> 12:00.220
We're trapped here
forever.

12:00.253 --> 12:03.056
Ooh. Does forever
include this weekend?

12:03.090 --> 12:04.958
'Cause the BET Awards
are on.

12:04.992 --> 12:06.726
Young Man:
BET Awards?

12:06.760 --> 12:08.295
I remember those.

12:08.328 --> 12:10.197
Those are
from the future.

12:10.230 --> 12:11.698
I need to get back
to the future.

12:11.731 --> 12:13.934
[ Gasps ]
"Back to the Future"!

12:13.967 --> 12:15.568
I love that movie!

12:15.602 --> 12:17.104
And Michael J. Fox!

12:17.137 --> 12:18.471
He was so great!

12:18.505 --> 12:21.775
Then [Gasps] that thing
happened to him.

12:21.809 --> 12:23.911
Oh, then the Towers.

12:23.944 --> 12:26.479
Then that pretty good
Denis Leary firemen show.

12:26.513 --> 12:29.282
I need to get back
to my time!

12:29.316 --> 12:31.785
It's not lighting up.
It's not lighting up!

12:31.819 --> 12:33.887
Oh, boy.

12:33.921 --> 12:35.823
He'll pay for that
at commercial time.

12:35.856 --> 12:37.557
What happens
at commercial?

12:37.590 --> 12:41.061
Technical Director:
And we're clear to commercial.

12:41.094 --> 12:44.164
[ Covax snarling, roaring ]
Young Man:
No! Please don't! Don't eat me!

12:44.197 --> 12:45.498
Stan: Yuh-oh.
No!

12:45.532 --> 12:48.268
No-o-o-o!!
Oh, boy.

12:48.301 --> 12:49.970
Sounds bad.
[ People whimpering, murmuring ]

12:50.003 --> 12:52.572
Technical Director:
We're on in 3, 2 --

12:52.605 --> 12:55.008
[ Jazzy piano music playing ]

12:55.042 --> 12:57.077
Oh, God. He's gone.

12:57.110 --> 12:59.346
It's a good thing
I'm clearly irreplaceable

12:59.379 --> 13:01.481
and integral to the show.

13:05.352 --> 13:07.587
[ Slow piano music playing ]

13:07.620 --> 13:11.358
♪♪

13:11.391 --> 13:15.495
Charlie, now how about
something a little harder?

13:15.528 --> 13:19.432
Here's a rowdy little number
called "Volcano Blast Freakout."

13:19.466 --> 13:23.136
[ Slow piano music continues ]

13:23.170 --> 13:25.138
Hot, hot, hot.

13:25.172 --> 13:27.841
Did you hear that guy say,
"Don't eat me"?

13:27.875 --> 13:29.877
That makes me think
Alistair ate him.

13:29.910 --> 13:32.980
He doesn't like it when
people mess up his show.

13:33.013 --> 13:35.548
You having
a nice time, Stan?

13:35.582 --> 13:37.717
[ Chuckles nervously ]
You know my name. That's cool!

13:37.750 --> 13:39.219
Hey, what is this place?

13:39.252 --> 13:42.722
This is a party, baby,
and parties are fun.

13:42.755 --> 13:46.726
So when the camera's on,
you will make nice conversation,

13:46.759 --> 13:48.728
you will keep
a drink in hand,

13:48.761 --> 13:51.731
and you will listen to
and love

13:51.764 --> 13:55.068
every bit of jazz
you hear.

13:55.102 --> 13:57.037
But I like swamp rock.

13:57.070 --> 13:59.006
-No.
-What if we want to leave?

13:59.039 --> 14:00.740
Leave? Why?

14:00.773 --> 14:02.242
You're with other
nighthawks,

14:02.275 --> 14:05.578
solo creatures who enjoy
mature pleasures.

14:05.612 --> 14:07.080
Face it, Stan.

14:07.114 --> 14:09.416
-You're a sensualist.
-I know.

14:09.449 --> 14:10.750
But I have a family.

14:10.783 --> 14:12.519
Do you, now?

14:12.552 --> 14:13.853
Yeah, I do.

14:13.887 --> 14:16.689
It's just hard to remember
their names.

14:16.723 --> 14:19.759
I told you.
I told you.

14:19.792 --> 14:21.528
Francine, Hayley,
Steve, Klaus,

14:21.561 --> 14:23.096
Roger. Good, good.

14:23.130 --> 14:24.998
Come on, Tuttle.
We can't forget.

14:25.032 --> 14:27.534
I can't remember
my family.

14:27.567 --> 14:29.336
-You don't have one.
-Oh.

14:29.369 --> 14:32.172
Don't worry.
I still have my family.

14:32.205 --> 14:34.207
We got to get out of here.

14:34.241 --> 14:36.443
But how?
You saw that guy.

14:36.476 --> 14:39.379
We can't call
the elevator.

14:39.412 --> 14:41.748
Maybe we don't have to.

14:41.781 --> 14:43.750
[ Elevator bell dinging ]

14:43.783 --> 14:45.785
[ Jazzy piano music playing ]

14:45.818 --> 14:48.956
[ Elevator bell dings ]

14:48.989 --> 14:50.290
Welcome --
Pardon. Pardon.
Excuse me.

14:50.323 --> 14:52.359
-Excuse me. Excuse me.
-I'm with him.

14:52.392 --> 15:00.233
♪♪

15:00.267 --> 15:08.141
♪♪

15:08.175 --> 15:10.243
I think we got away!

15:13.280 --> 15:14.381
It's all fake!

15:14.414 --> 15:16.216
Let's try the soup.

15:16.249 --> 15:18.651
That's how you can tell
if it's a real diner.

15:18.685 --> 15:20.287
We're still on the show.

15:20.320 --> 15:21.388
Stan, look!

15:21.421 --> 15:23.490
The tree!

15:23.523 --> 15:26.393
Follow the color!

15:26.426 --> 15:27.494
This is the way home!

15:27.527 --> 15:31.231
Langley Falls,
here we come!

15:31.264 --> 15:32.966
And maybe there was
something appealing

15:33.000 --> 15:34.667
about that bachelor vibe.

15:34.701 --> 15:37.637
Because, boy, the family
was driving me nuts.

15:37.670 --> 15:39.506
You wouldn't know
what that's like, but trust me.

15:39.539 --> 15:42.175
I pretend my fingers
are my family --

15:42.209 --> 15:44.177
Mama Thumb
always nagging,

15:44.211 --> 15:46.679
Uncle Index
with the corny jokes.

15:46.713 --> 15:48.115
What can I say?

15:48.148 --> 15:49.916
They're a handful!

15:49.949 --> 15:52.185
[ Swamp rock music playing ]
Stan: ♪ I got Francine

15:52.219 --> 15:53.620
♪ I got Steve

15:53.653 --> 15:55.655
♪ Uh, I got Harley

15:55.688 --> 15:57.757
♪ I got Clark,
I want to say Bruce ♪

15:57.790 --> 15:58.958
Take it, Tuttle!

15:58.992 --> 16:00.660
Tuttle:
♪ I got no one

16:00.693 --> 16:02.295
Take it, Stan!

16:02.329 --> 16:05.198
♪♪

16:05.232 --> 16:07.267
Welp, see you around the
neighborhood, Tuttle, old boy.

16:07.300 --> 16:10.503
Yeah.
I should get going, too.

16:10.537 --> 16:12.339
Oh, yeah.
You have nobody.

16:12.372 --> 16:14.041
Turn off the car,
you idiot.

16:14.074 --> 16:16.276
You're coming inside,
you big, fat idiot.

16:16.309 --> 16:17.710
[ Gasps ]
You mean it?

16:17.744 --> 16:19.646
Yeah.
You live with me now.

16:19.679 --> 16:21.614
I'll convert the shed
into a room for you.

16:21.648 --> 16:24.684
-I won't insulate it.
-Stan, I have a house.

16:24.717 --> 16:27.054
It's nothing. You'll sleep
on some old car batteries.

16:27.087 --> 16:28.488
I won't hear
another word.

16:28.521 --> 16:30.657
Now come watch me
hug my family.

16:30.690 --> 16:33.360
Beloved ones, I'm home!

16:33.393 --> 16:35.195
[ Jazzy piano music playing ]

16:35.228 --> 16:37.030
Welcome back, nighthawks.

16:37.064 --> 16:38.698
We've been expecting you.

16:38.731 --> 16:43.870
♪♪

16:43.903 --> 16:47.307
Oh, no. I'm gonna
forget them forever.

16:47.340 --> 16:55.148
♪♪

16:55.182 --> 17:02.922
♪♪

17:02.955 --> 17:10.763
♪♪

17:10.797 --> 17:13.600
Have you heard the new hi-fi's
with the quadraphonic sound?

17:13.633 --> 17:16.436
They're really the best
for listening to jazz.

17:16.469 --> 17:19.739
It sounds like,
"Skeedle-dee-deep-do-bop-do-bop,

17:19.772 --> 17:24.077
scoop-doop, sly-gar,
flarga-marga, smee-boo."

17:24.111 --> 17:26.179
A man can't be himself
in the kitchen.

17:26.213 --> 17:28.348
It's not his domain.

17:28.381 --> 17:32.385
But what about when he gets
hungry, and she's not there?

17:32.419 --> 17:35.788
Well, the space-age
wet bar of tomorrow

17:35.822 --> 17:38.057
can satisfy his hunger.

17:38.091 --> 17:40.960
A Rumaki-Maker-Matic,
folks.

17:40.993 --> 17:44.131
Just plug it in, load the hopper
with chicken liver,

17:44.164 --> 17:47.066
and within minutes,
nuclear-hot hors d'oeuvres

17:47.100 --> 17:48.535
plop out all over

17:48.568 --> 17:51.771
this green tray
that looks like a cabbage.

17:51.804 --> 17:54.474
-Ah!
-Ooh!

17:54.507 --> 17:56.476
Now, picture it.
It's 11:15.

17:56.509 --> 17:58.278
You're at the Sands.

17:58.311 --> 18:01.881
Frank Sinatra's overflow girls
are starting to get hungry.

18:01.914 --> 18:04.484
They say they want melted
cheese and lots of it.

18:04.517 --> 18:06.953
Time for fondue.

18:06.986 --> 18:08.288
Fondue.

18:08.321 --> 18:09.989
With an electric
fondue set,

18:10.022 --> 18:11.991
it's fast,
it's easy and clean,

18:12.024 --> 18:14.093
and lets you
eat more cheese

18:14.127 --> 18:16.629
more quickly
than ever before.

18:16.663 --> 18:18.598
Fondue! Fondue.

18:18.631 --> 18:20.133
Electric fondue!

18:20.167 --> 18:22.101
Bingo-bango,
hot cheese on tap!

18:22.135 --> 18:24.003
My wife!
My wife, Fondue!

18:24.036 --> 18:25.905
No, Fondine.
Francine!

18:25.938 --> 18:29.842
I remember Francine, and, oh,
how she loved her fondue!

18:29.876 --> 18:30.977
Tuttle! Wake up!

18:31.010 --> 18:32.679
-[ Screaming ]
-Francine!

18:32.712 --> 18:34.181
Hayley! Steve!

18:34.214 --> 18:36.416
Klaus! Roger!

18:36.449 --> 18:37.950
I'm not a nighthawk!

18:37.984 --> 18:39.986
I want my family!

18:42.222 --> 18:44.291
We're going to take
a commercial break,

18:44.324 --> 18:47.627
and when we return,
I promise the party will be...

18:47.660 --> 18:49.529
back on track.

18:49.562 --> 18:50.863
Stan, are you okay?

18:50.897 --> 18:53.366
You're wearing the wall
like a hat.

18:53.400 --> 18:54.667
Whoa.

18:54.701 --> 18:57.804
♪♪

18:57.837 --> 19:00.139
I came in
through the static.

19:00.173 --> 19:02.008
This is the way out!

19:02.041 --> 19:04.711
♪♪

19:04.744 --> 19:07.013
Technical Director:
And we're clear to commercial.

19:07.046 --> 19:10.283
♪♪

19:10.317 --> 19:11.818
[ Snarling ]

19:11.851 --> 19:13.820
♪♪

19:13.853 --> 19:15.488
[ Continues snarling ]

19:15.522 --> 19:24.864
♪♪

19:24.897 --> 19:28.167
[ Tapping ]

19:28.201 --> 19:30.570
[ Gasps ]

19:30.603 --> 19:32.038
Let go of me, you monster!

19:32.071 --> 19:34.841
Tuttle: Ow! Stan,
you're kicking my face!

19:34.874 --> 19:38.911
♪♪

19:38.945 --> 19:40.513
Oh! We're safe.

19:40.547 --> 19:41.548
He can't get past the --

19:41.581 --> 19:42.849
[ Covax roars ]

19:42.882 --> 19:44.217
[ Both scream ]

19:44.251 --> 19:46.353
[ Screaming ]

19:46.386 --> 19:49.222
♪♪

19:52.058 --> 19:54.627
[ Singsong voice ]
Look what I did!

19:56.263 --> 19:57.397
Where the hell
have you been?

19:57.430 --> 19:58.898
I almost
went down there.

19:58.931 --> 20:01.434
Family!
Oh, sweet family!

20:01.468 --> 20:03.703
I want you to know that
I haven't forgotten you,

20:03.736 --> 20:05.238
even if I came close.

20:05.272 --> 20:09.108
I'm here now, and I want to do
what you want to do.

20:09.141 --> 20:11.944
I want to raise this child.

20:11.978 --> 20:14.046
-Daddy's here.
-I'm not doing that anymore.

20:14.080 --> 20:15.348
Thank God.
[ Thud ]

20:15.382 --> 20:17.183
[ Both grunting ]

20:17.216 --> 20:22.389
♪♪

20:22.422 --> 20:27.560
♪♪

20:27.594 --> 20:29.028
Poor bastard.

20:29.061 --> 20:31.197
Feels good to have things
back to normal.

20:31.230 --> 20:32.799
-Stan?
-Whaddup?

20:32.832 --> 20:37.537
Have you heard the new hi-fi's
with quadraphonic sound?

20:37.570 --> 20:39.406
They're the best hi-fi's
for...

20:39.439 --> 20:41.574
-Ja-a-a-zz.
-Ja-a-a-zz.

20:41.608 --> 20:44.143
No. No! No!

20:44.176 --> 20:46.446
No-o-o-o!

20:46.479 --> 20:49.115
Announcer:
That's right! "American Dad!"
is now a show that exists

20:49.148 --> 20:54.487
on TV in the basement of
the family of "American Dad!"

20:54.521 --> 20:56.088
Another great episode.

20:56.122 --> 20:58.825
So long, nighthawks.

20:58.858 --> 21:02.161
♪♪

21:02.194 --> 21:04.130
Bye! Have a beautiful time!
